China to Scrap PCR Test For Inbound Travelers in Latest Easing:Source1. China will no longer require travelers to the country to provide a negative PCR test result  scrapping a rule thatâ€™s been a major deterrent for visitation since the worldâ€™s second-largest economy emerged from Covid isolation in January.2. From April 29  travelers can instead show negative rapid antigen test results while airlines wonâ€™t be required to check the proof  Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Mao Ning said Tuesday at a regular press briefing in Beijing.3. The country earlier loosened the rule for some countries like New Zealand and Malaysia. The move to scrap it entirely comes as air travel in and out of China recovers at a sluggish pace  with the number of international flights in the first quarter only at 12.4% of the 2019 level  government data showed.More here
